        "# E-commerce Text Classification Project\n",
        "\n",
        "**Author:** [Your Name]\n",
        "**Date:** 26-10-2025\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1. Business Understanding\n",
        "\n",
        "**Problem:**\n",
        "This project aims to solve a common e-commerce challenge: automatically categorizing products based on their descriptions. Manually sorting thousands of products is time-consuming and prone to error.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Objective:**\n",
        "The goal is to build and evaluate several machine learning and deep learning models to accurately classify a given product **\"Description\"** into its correct **\"Category\"**.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Success Metric:**\n",
        "The primary metric for success will be **accuracy**, which measures the percentage of products classified correctly.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Models to be Trained:**\n",
        "1.  **Classical ML:**\n",
        "    * Logistic Regression\n",
        "    * Multinomial Naive Bayes\n",
        "    * Support Vector Machines (SVM)\n",
        "    * Random Forest\n",
        "    * K-Nearest Neighbours (KNN)\n",
        "2.  **Deep Learning:**\n",
        "    * Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Methodology:**\n",
        "We will follow the CRISP-DM (Cross-Industry Standard Process for Data Mining) framework."

        "# --- Phase 1 & 2: Business and Data Understanding ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Import necessary libraries\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import nltk\n",
        "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
        "from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set up plotting style\n",
        "%matplotlib inline\n",
        "sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Download NLTK assets (only need to run once)\n",
        "nltk.download('stopwords')\n",
        "nltk.download('wordnet')\n",
        "nltk.download('omw-1.4')\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 2. Data Understanding ---\n",
        "# Load the dataset\n",
        "# !!! IMPORTANT: Update 'ecommerce_data.csv' to your file's name !!!\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    df = pd.read_csv('/content/ecommerce_data.csv')\n",
        "    print(\"Dataset loaded successfully!\")\n",
        "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
        "    print(\"Error: Dataset file not found. Please check the filename and upload it to Colab.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the first 5 rows\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Data Head ---\")\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display concise summary of the dataframe\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Data Info ---\")\n",
        "df.info()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check for missing values\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Missing Values ---\")\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check the distribution of the target variable 'Category'\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Category Distribution ---\")\n",
        "print(df['Category'].value_counts())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the category distribution\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "sns.countplot(y=df['Category'], order = df['Category'].value_counts().index)\n",
        "plt.title('Distribution of Product Categories')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Category')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- 3. Data Preparation (Part 1: Cleaning) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Fix CSV Loading Issue ---\n",
        "# We know we only need the first two columns (0 and 1)\n",
        "# 'usecols' parameter avoids loading the 201 junk 'Unnamed' columns.\n",
        "# 'on_bad_lines'='skip' will skip any rows that are completely malformed.\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    df = pd.read_csv('ecommerce_data.csv', usecols=[0, 1], on_bad_lines='skip')\n",
        "    print(\"Dataset re-loaded successfully using 'usecols' and 'on_bad_lines'.\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"Error re-loading data: {e}\")\n",
        "    # If this fails, we might need a different encoding\n",
        "    # df = pd.read_csv('ecommerce_data.csv', usecols=[0, 1], on_bad_lines='skip', encoding='ISO-8859-1')\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Fix Column Name Issue ---\n",
        "# The original column names have trailing spaces (e.g., 'Category ').\n",
        "# .str.strip() removes all leading/trailing whitespace from names.\n",
        "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()\n",
        "print(f\"\\nCleaned column names: {df.columns.to_list()}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Fix Missing Values Issue ---\n",
        "# Drop rows where 'Description' or 'Category' is missing\n",
        "print(f\"\\nShape before dropping NaN: {df.shape}\")\n",
        "df.dropna(subset=['Description', 'Category'], inplace=True)\n",
        "print(f\"Shape after dropping NaN: {df.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Verification Step ---\n",
        "# Now we verify that our cleaning worked.\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Check Info (Should now show 2 columns)\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- (CLEANED) Data Info ---\")\n",
        "df.info()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Check for Missing Values (Should now be 0)\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- (CLEANED) Missing Values ---\")\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Check Category Distribution (This should work now!)\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- (CLEANED) Category Distribution ---\")\n",
        "print(df['Category'].value_counts())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the cleaned category distribution\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "sns.countplot(y=df['Category'], order = df['Category'].value_counts().index)\n",
        "plt.title('Distribution of Product Categories (Cleaned)')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Category')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],

        "# --- 3. Data Preparation (Part 2: Text Preprocessing) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize the lemmatizer and stop words list\n",
        "lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
        "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))\n",
        "\n",
        "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Cleans and preprocesses a single text string.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # 1. Lowercase\n",
        "    text = text.lower()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 2. Remove punctuation and numbers (keep only letters)\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\\s]', '', text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 3. Tokenize (split into words)\n",
        "    tokens = text.split()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 4. Remove Stopwords and 5. Lemmatize\n",
        "    processed_tokens = []\n",
        "    for word in tokens:\n",
        "        if word not in stop_words:\n",
        "            lemmatized_word = lemmatizer.lemmatize(word)\n",
        "            processed_tokens.append(lemmatized_word)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 6. Re-join words into a single string\n",
        "    return ' '.join(processed_tokens)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Apply the function to our 'Description' column ---\n",
        "print(\"Starting text preprocessing. This may take a minute...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a new column 'processed_description'\n",
        "# We use .copy() to avoid a common pandas warning (SettingWithCopyWarning)\n",
        "df_clean = df.copy()\n",
        "df_clean['processed_description'] = df_clean['Description'].apply(preprocess_text)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Preprocessing complete.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Verification Step ---\n",
        "# Let's check the 'before' and 'after' for a few samples\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Preprocessing Examples ---\")\n",
        "for i in [0, 1, 2]:\n",
        "    print(f\"Original:    {df_clean['Description'].iloc[i]}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Processed:   {df_clean['processed_description'].iloc[i]}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the head of our new, clean dataframe\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Cleaned Dataframe Head ---\")\n",
        "print(df_clean.head())"

        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 3. Data Preparation (Part 3: Feature Engineering) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Define Features (X) and Target (y)\n",
        "X = df_clean['processed_description']\n",
        "y = df_clean['Category']\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Encode the Target (y)\n",
        "# We create a new column for the encoded labels for clarity\n",
        "le = LabelEncoder()\n",
        "df_clean['category_encoded'] = le.fit_transform(y)\n",
        "y_encoded = df_clean['category_encoded']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Store the mapping from number to category name for later\n",
        "# We can access this with le.classes_\n",
        "print(\"--- Label Encoding ---\")\n",
        "for i, category in enumerate(le.classes_):\n",
        "    print(f\"{category} --> {i}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Split the data\n",
        "# We split into 80% training and 20% testing\n",
        "# random_state=42 ensures we get the same \"random\" split every time we run this\n",
        "# stratify=y_encoded ensures our train/test sets have the *same percentage*\n",
        "# of each category. This is CRITICAL for imbalanced datasets!\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X,\n",
        "    y_encoded,\n",
        "    test_size=0.2,\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    stratify=y_encoded\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n--- Data Split ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Training data shape: {X_train.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Testing data shape: {X_test.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Training labels shape: {y_train.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Testing labels shape: {y_test.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Apply TF-IDF Vectorization\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- TF-IDF Vectorization ---\")\n",
        "# Initialize the vectorizer\n",
        "# max_features=5000 means we only keep the top 5000 most important words.\n",
        "# This saves memory and can prevent overfitting.\n",
        "tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- IMPORTANT FOUNDATION CONCEPT ---\n",
        "# We 'fit_transform' on the training data. This 'fit' step\n",
        "# learns the vocabulary (the 5000 words) from the training data only.\n",
        "X_train_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# We ONLY 'transform' on the test data. This uses the *same*\n",
        "# vocabulary learned from the training data to convert the\n",
        "# test text into numbers.\n",
        "# We NEVER 'fit' on test data. That would be \"cheating\" (data leakage).\n",
        "X_test_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.transform(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the results\n",
        "print(f\"Shape of X_train_tfidf: {X_train_tfidf.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Shape of X_test_tfidf: {X_test_tfidf.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"This means we have {X_train_tfidf.shape[0]} training samples and {X_train_tfidf.shape[1]} unique words (features).\")"
      ],

        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Embedding, LSTM, Dense, SpatialDropout1D, Bidirectional\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 4. Modeling (Q6: Deep Learning Model) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"--- 6. Deep Learning (LSTM) ---\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 1. Import all modules (done above) ---\n",
        "# --- 2. Build the model architecture ---\n",
        "print(\"Building the LSTM model...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "EMBEDDING_DIM = 128 # The size of the word-vector for each word\n",
        "\n",
        "model = Sequential()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Layer 1: Embedding Layer\n",
        "# input_dim = 10000 (our max vocab size)\n",
        "# output_dim = 128 (the size of the embedding vector)\n",
        "# input_length = 195 (the length of our padded sequences)\n",
        "model.add(Embedding(\n",
        "    input_dim=MAX_VOCAB_SIZE,\n",
        "    output_dim=EMBEDDING_DIM,\n",
        "    input_length=MAX_SEQ_LENGTH\n",
        "))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Layer 2: Dropout\n",
        "# This helps prevent overfitting\n",
        "model.add(SpatialDropout1D(0.2))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Layer 3: LSTM Layer\n",
        "# We'll use 100 \"memory units\"\n",
        "model.add(LSTM(100, dropout=0.2, recurrent_dropout=0.2))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Layer 4: Final Output Layer\n",
        "# We have 4 classes, so 4 neurons\n",
        "# 'softmax' activation gives us the class probabilities\n",
        "model.add(Dense(4, activation='softmax'))\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 3. Compile the model ---\n",
        "# 'categorical_crossentropy' is the standard loss function for multi-class classification\n",
        "# 'adam' is an efficient, all-purpose optimizer\n",
        "# 'accuracy' is what we'll monitor\n",
        "model.compile(\n",
        "    loss='categorical_crossentropy',\n",
        "    optimizer='adam',\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- 4. Modeling (Q6: Training and Plotting) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# We'll use 10% of our training data as a \"validation\" set\n",
        "# The model will check its performance on this set after each epoch.\n",
        "# This is what EarlyStopping will monitor.\n",
        "VALIDATION_SPLIT = 0.1\n",
        "EPOCHS = 10\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE = 64 # Process data in batches of 64 samples\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Define EarlyStopping callback\n",
        "# This will stop training if the 'val_loss' doesn't improve for 2 epochs\n",
        "early_stop = EarlyStopping(\n",
        "    monitor='val_loss',\n",
        "    patience=2,\n",
        "    restore_best_weights=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Starting Model Training ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"This will run for up to {EPOCHS} epochs, but may stop early.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Run the model (fit the data)\n",
        "# This is the step that actually trains the model.\n",
        "history = model.fit(\n",
        "    X_train_pad,\n",
        "    y_train_cat,\n",
        "    epochs=EPOCHS,\n",
        "    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n",
        "    validation_split=VALIDATION_SPLIT,\n",
        "    callbacks=[early_stop]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Model Training Complete ---\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 4. Draw validation and train accuracy plots ---\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Plotting Accuracy and Loss ---\")\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_history(history_data):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Plots training & validation accuracy and loss.\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get the metrics\n",
        "    acc = history_data.history['accuracy']\n",
        "    val_acc = history_data.history['val_accuracy']\n",
        "    loss = history_data.history['loss']\n",
        "    val_loss = history_data.history['val_loss']\n",
        "    epochs_range = range(len(acc))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot Accuracy\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs_range, acc, label='Training Accuracy')\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_acc, label='Validation Accuracy')\n",
        "    plt.legend(loc='lower right')\n",
        "    plt.title('Training and Validation Accuracy')\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot Loss\n",
        "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs_range, loss, label='Training Loss')\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_loss, label='Validation Loss')\n",
        "    plt.legend(loc='upper right')\n",
        "    plt.title('Training and Validation Loss')\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Call the plotting function\n",
        "plot_history(history)"
      ],

        "# --- 5. Evaluation (Q6: Final Evaluation on Test Set) ---\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"--- Evaluating Deep Learning Model on Test Set ---\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Get the final loss and accuracy\n",
        "test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(X_test_pad, y_test_cat, verbose=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTest Accuracy: {test_accuracy * 100:.2f}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test Loss: {test_loss:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Store this in our results summary\n",
        "results_summary['LSTM (Deep Learning)'] = test_accuracy\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Get predictions\n",
        "# model.predict gives probabilities (due to softmax)\n",
        "y_pred_probs = model.predict(X_test_pad)\n",
        "\n",
        "# We must convert these probabilities back to single-digit labels (0, 1, 2, or 3)\n",
        "# np.argmax finds the index (0, 1, 2, or 3) with the highest probability\n",
        "y_pred_dl = np.argmax(y_pred_probs, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Generate Classification Report and Confusion Matrix\n",
        "# Remember, y_test is our *original* non-one-hot-encoded test labels\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Classification Report (LSTM) ---\")\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_dl, target_names=le.classes_))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Confusion Matrix (LSTM) ---\")\n",
        "cm_dl = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_dl)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the confusion matrix\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "sns.heatmap(cm_dl, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',\n",
        "            xticklabels=le.classes_, yticklabels=le.classes_)\n",
        "plt.title('LSTM Model Confusion Matrix')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Actual Category')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Predicted Category')\n",
        "plt.show()"
